fgets() - read a line from a file stream

- API
    char *fgets(char *s, int size, FILE *stream);

- RETURN VALUE
    returns s on success, NULL if error or end of file

- include
    #include <stdio.h>

- example - read file line by line
    while (fgets(buf, BUFMAX, fp))
        printf("%s\n", buf); //prints each line